-- Kenya Remittances Increased 39% to $81.3 Million in October
-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 2011-12-19T11:23:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/kenya-remittances-increased-39-to-81-3-million-in-october-1-.html
Remittances from Kenyans working
abroad rose 39 percent in October from a year earlier to $81.3
million, the central bank said.  Remittances to  East Africa ’s largest economy climbed to
$725.1 million in the first 10 months of the year, 13 percent
above all of last year’s $641.9 million, the Nairobi-based
Central Bank of Kenya said in a statement on its website today.  Kenya relied on  North America  for 47 percent of its
 remittances  in October and Europe for 29 percent, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
